; idempotency_e2e.beancount — fictional ledger for the Reducer
; reduce/interpolation idempotency test.
;
; All account names and commodity symbols in this file are invented for
; testing purposes. No real-world brokers, funds, or tickers are
; referenced. USD is used as a neutral cash currency.
;
; The fixture exercises every Pass-2 interpolation/synthesis path the
; Reducer can take, in a single ledger:
;
;   (A) Deferred per-unit cost on an augmenting `{}` posting. Pass 2
;       solves PerUnit from the residual.
;   (B) Multi-lot reduction Total synthesis: a `{}` reduction crosses
;       a lot boundary under FIFO and the Reducer writes back
;       Cost.Total = Σ |units| × lot.Number.
;   (C) Auto-balanced posting (nil Amount) inferred from the residual.
;
; (B) and (C) coexist on the same transaction so a single sale drives
; both edits.
;
; A trivial cash-only transaction is also included so the test exercises
; the no-clone path (needsBookingClone == false) alongside the cloned
; transactions.

option "title" "Reducer Idempotency Fixture"
option "operating_currency" "USD"

2024-12-01 open Assets:Cash               USD
2024-12-01 open Assets:Stock              STOCK   "FIFO"
2024-12-01 open Income:Capital            USD
2024-12-01 open Expenses:Food             USD
2024-12-01 open Equity:Opening-Balances

2024-12-31 * "Opening cash balance"
  Assets:Cash                 1000.00 USD
  Equity:Opening-Balances    -1000.00 USD

; (A) Deferred cost: the augmenting STOCK posting has a `{}` cost spec
; with no number. Pass 2 divides the residual (-(-50.00) = 50.00 USD)
; by the 10-unit Amount to solve PerUnit = 5.00 USD per share.
2025-01-10 * "Buy STOCK with deferred cost"
  Assets:Stock                     10 STOCK {}
  Assets:Cash                  -50.00 USD

; A second lot priced explicitly. Together with the previous buy this
; sets up a two-lot inventory at differing per-unit costs, which the
; sale below crosses under FIFO.
2025-02-15 * "Buy STOCK second lot"
  Assets:Stock                     10 STOCK {6.00 USD}
  Assets:Cash                  -60.00 USD

; (B) + (C): selling 15 STOCK under `{}` consumes 10 from the first lot
; (5.00 USD basis) and 5 from the second lot (6.00 USD basis), for a
; total cost basis of 10*5 + 5*6 = 80.00 USD. Pass 1 writes that figure
; back as Cost.Total. The cash leg is explicit at +100.00 USD, so the
; auto-balanced Income:Capital posting absorbs the realized gain
; (residual = -20.00 USD).
2025-03-01 * "Sell STOCK at gain"
  Assets:Stock                    -15 STOCK {}
  Assets:Cash                  100.00 USD
  Income:Capital

; A purely cash transaction with no cost specs and no auto-balanced
; posting. needsBookingClone returns false here, so the Reducer reuses
; the input pointer in its output — exercising the non-cloning branch
; in the same fixture.
2025-03-15 * "Lunch"
  Expenses:Food                 12.00 USD
  Assets:Cash                  -12.00 USD
